Philippine Stocks: Aboitiz Power Corp., Philex Mining Corp.

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-03-07T03:07:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/philippine-stocks-aboitiz-power-corp-philex-mining-corp-.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual price changes in Philippine trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses, and prices are as of 10:36 a.m. in
Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 12.19, or 0.3
percent, to 3,894.90    Aboitiz Power Corp. (AP)  , an owner of  power plants  and
electricity retailer, gained 1 percent to 31.20 pesos, set for
the highest close since Jan. 4. Therma Marine Inc., a unit of
Aboitiz Power, sought approval for two electricity supply
agreements, the Philippine Daily Inquirer reported, citing
documents filed with a regulator. Chairman Enrique Aboitiz
couldn’t be reached in his office for comment.    Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  , the largest Philippine metals
producer, climbed for a fifth day, advancing 1.1 percent to
14.62 pesos. It’s the stock’s longest rally since Dec. 23.
Philex is budgeting 3 billion pesos ($69 million) for capital
expenditure this year and is “looking at other mines or
properties that it can operate as part of its strategy for
growth,” a stock-exchange filing showed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in  Manila  at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  